==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trunk piston
<hw>Trunk piston</hw>. <def>In a single-acting engine, an elongated
hollow piston, open at the end, in which the end of the connecting rod
is pivoted. The piston rod, crosshead and stuffing box are thus
dispensed with.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trunk steamer</ent>⟦br⟧
